## üö´ Anti-Patterns to Avoid

### Testing Anti-Patterns
- ‚ùå **Don't test implementation details** - test behavior, not internal state
- ‚ùå **Don't use complex mocks** - prefer simple, predictable mocks
- ‚ùå **Don't test multiple concerns** in a single test
- ‚ùå **Don't write to production files** during testing

### Component Anti-Patterns
- ‚ùå **Don't create overly complex components** - split into smaller components
- ‚ùå **Don't use inline styles** - use CSS classes or styled components
- ‚ùå **Don't ignore accessibility** - always include proper ARIA attributes
- ‚ùå **Don't use any type** - always define proper TypeScript types

### State Management Anti-Patterns
- ‚ùå **Don't mutate state directly** - use immutable update patterns
- ‚ùå **Don't store derived state** - compute it when needed
- ‚ùå **Don't pass props through multiple levels** - use context for deep prop drilling

